article.headline: Army 53, VMI 49
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Jarell Brown scored 21, including a basket to take the lead with 2 seconds left, to lead Army to a 53-49 win over VMI Monday night. VMI (0-1) jumped out to a six-point advantage, but Army (2-1) took the lead on Brown's 3-pointer to make it 18-17 with 4:50 left in the half. Reggie Williams' 3-pointer at the buzzer brought VMI to within one at 22-21 at the break. Williams sank two free throws to regain the lead with 17:13 remaining. Chavis Holmes' 3-pointer put the Keydets up by six at 41-35 with 7:13 left. Eight straight points from Brown tied it at 43 with 3:23 left, and Brown helped Army regain the lead again off a 3-pointer with 1:15 left that put it at 49-47. Williams again tied it off free throws, but Brown answered with a basket that put Army up with 2 seconds left. Mars Jackson stole the ball and made a layup at the buzzer to seal the victory. Williams led VMI with 22 points, including four from outside the arc. Brown had five 3-pointers for Army, and Corban Bates added five steals.
